### 2. Backend Access Restrictions & Security Guards
Protect endpoints at the API layer so that unauthorized requests are rejected and sensitive data is not leaked over the network.

#### [MODIFY] [reports.controller.ts](file:///c:/MANAS/Projects/LK/Implementation/backend/src/features/reports/reports.controller.ts)
- In `getDashboardStats`, inspect `req.user?.role`. If the user is not an owner (`!== 'owner'`), nullify the `inventoryValue` property in the response.

#### [MODIFY] [products.controller.ts](file:///c:/MANAS/Projects/LK/Implementation/backend/src/features/products/products.controller.ts)
- In `getAllProducts` and `getProductById`, inspect `req.user?.role`. If the user is not an owner, sanitize all returned product objects by removing or nullifying the `cost_price` field.
- In `updateProduct`, inspect `req.user?.role`. If a staff member tries to update the `is_active` status of a product, reject the request with `403 Forbidden`.

#### [MODIFY] [billing.routes.ts](file:///c:/MANAS/Projects/LK/Implementation/backend/src/features/billing/billing.routes.ts)
- In `GET /` (list bills), if the user is not an owner:
  - Enforce a 7-day query constraint: calculate the date 7 days ago and enforce that `date_from` query parameter is capped at most to 7 days ago.
- In `GET /:id` (get single bill), inspect `req.user?.role`. If the user is not an owner, nullify or remove `cost_price` from all nested items in `bill_items`.

#### [MODIFY] [billing.service.ts](file:///c:/MANAS/Projects/LK/Implementation/backend/src/features/billing/billing.service.ts)
- Update `getBills` to accept the user's role and omit/nullify the `cost_price` field inside `bill_items` if the role is not `'owner'`.

#### [MODIFY] [khata.routes.ts](file:///c:/MANAS/Projects/LK/Implementation/backend/src/features/khata/khata.routes.ts)
- Add `requireOwner` middleware guard to the Customer Repayment route `POST /:id/repay` to block staff members from logging customer repayments.

#### [MODIFY] [purchases.routes.ts](file:///c:/MANAS/Projects/LK/Implementation/backend/src/features/purchases/purchases.routes.ts)
- Add `requireOwner` middleware guard to the Supplier Repayment route `POST /suppliers/:id/repay` to block staff members from logging supplier repayments.
- Add `requireOwner` middleware guard to all other `/purchases` endpoints if necessary (e.g. GET `/`, POST `/` for purchase orders, expenses, suppliers list/creation) to prevent staff from viewing or adding supplier debt, expenses, and cost price details.

